      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>There has been some really great learn to play the guitar posts over the last 4 weeks. Here is a selection of some of the better ones.:</div>
<ul style='padding-left:10px;padding-right:10px;margin-top:15px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px'>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/learn-electric-guitar/basic-electric-guitar' style='color:#0000FF'>Basic Electric Guitar</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Wednesday, April 1st, 2009 in <a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/?cat=4'>learn electric guitar</a> - Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>You can learn basic electric guitar quite easily. All you really need is a guitar, an amplifier or a computer (or both) and a good home study guide or multimedia course.If you are even the slightest bit musically inclined then you will probably be able to pick it up quite quickly. The guitar is one of the easiest instruments to get started with and you can be playing chords and accompanying songs in a very short time.One of the main difficulties with the electric guitar is progressing from this basic guitar stage to a more advanced level of playing.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/learn-electric-guitar/guitar-beginners' style='color:#0000FF'>Which Guitar For Beginners</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Wednesday, April 1st, 2009 in <a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/?cat=4'>learn electric guitar</a> - Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Here is a great <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamorama1.html"  rel='nofollow' >guitar for beginners</a> to <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamorama1.html"  rel='nofollow' >learn electric guitar</a>. Its not your cheapest foreign import guitar but a quality Fender guitar. This model is a good quality instrument for beginners and well suited to all styles of music. The amazon offer here includes the guitar, an amplifier, a 10-watt Squier amp with 10-foot cord, strings, picks, strap, gigbag, guitar stand, and instructional DVD. All that you need to get you started.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/learn-electric-guitar/teach-electric-guitar' style='color:#0000FF'>teach yourself electric guitar</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Friday, April 3rd, 2009 in <a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/?cat=4'>learn electric guitar</a> - Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Is it really possible to teach yourself electric guitar?People have been teaching themselves to play the electric guitar for years and more so than any other instrument, is is very common for most guitarists to be self taught.Taking private lessons has always been a good idea but today with all of the multimedia courses available on the Internet it is very feasible to advance to quite a high level on your own. The video and audio examples if followed correctly will teach you the basics of guitar playing, show you the correct posture, how to hold your hands and which fingers to use etc.Download a multimedia home study course and teach yourself electric guitar today.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/guitar-lessons-for-beginners/play-guitar-beginners' style='color:#0000FF'>How To Play Guitar for beginners</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Thursday, April 2nd, 2009 in <a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/?cat=3'>guitar lessons for beginners</a> - Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>There are many books on how to play <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamorama1.html"  rel='nofollow' >guitar for beginners</a> and recently there have been many audio visual courses released on the market too.A few years ago, it was always advisable to find a professional teacher to give you private lessons but nowadays you can learn very efficiently and quickly by following audio and video examples of how to play.The multimedia courses on how to play guitar are mostly available on DVDs but there are an ever increasing number of these home study courses that are making their content available for immediate download online.Most of these beginner guitar courses offer free trials where they send you the first few lessons for free so you can check them out.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/learn-electric-guitar/learn-electric-guitar-april-4-2009' style='color:#0000FF'>Learn Electric Guitar - April 4, 2009</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Saturday, April 4th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/?cat=4'>learn electric guitar</a> - Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Mar 24, Electric guitar circuitryApril 2, 2009 - Ever wondered about the circuitry inside your electric guitar? Check out this article for all the relevant information.Beginner <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamorama1.html"  rel='nofollow' >guitar lessons</a> online for free?April 2, 2009 - Take a look at these free introductory <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamorama1.html"  rel='nofollow' >guitar lessons</a> available onlineHow to play Black Sabath’s Paranoid on GUITAR w/ Tabs!April 2, 2009 - Guitar tabs for the epic rock theme, Paranoid by Black Sabbath*Easy* to Learn *Guitar Songs* - Getting LessonsApril 2, 2009 - Here is a selection of some easy to <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamoramaacoustic1.html"  rel='nofollow' >learn acoustic guitar</a> songs - easily laid out for beginner guitarists to learn.</div>
</li>
</ul>
<div>Which post was your favorite? Let s know below.</div>
