      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Some <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamoramaacoustic1.html"  rel='nofollow' >acoustic guitar basics</a> are all that is needed when you first pick up a guitar before you can be playing along to a wide variety of songs.</p>
<p>It can be really easy to learn three or four simple chords and a simple strumming rhythm. This is really all that is needed to be able to accompany a wide range of songs. Most popular songs only use three or four chords and can be renditioned quite effectively on a basic <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamoramaacoustic1.html"  rel='nofollow' >acoustic guitar</a>.</p>
<p>One of the joys of an <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamoramaacoustic1.html"  rel='nofollow' >acoustic guitar</a> is that the simple chords can sound so full when you strum all of the strings and the guitar basics are really easy to pick up and learn.</p>
