      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Most songs you hear can be adapted to become easy strumming guitar songs. You could go out and buy some songbooks but they often contain complex arrangements and tricky guitar chords.</p>
<p>You could also listen to the original songs and try to copy the guitar playing but more often than not although you manage to fathom out the chords or the notes it doesn&#8217;t seem to sound the same.</p>
<p>The fact is that most songs can be played by using just a few simple basic chords and there is no need to over complicate things by playing tricky arrangements. This is very important when you are beginning, especially for children so as not to get disheartened.</p>
<p>This post via the  <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com">Learn Guitar</a> blog where you can get detailed information on how to learn electric guitar and how to learn acoustic guitar.</p>
