      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If you do a web search for electric <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamorama1.html"  rel='nofollow' >guitar for beginners</a> you will come up with hundreds of pages all offering guitar courses. Most of these will be for home study consisting of Cd&#8217;s and videos or even downloadable versions which can be purchased immediately online.</p>
<p>These courses can be quite good and you can progress from absolute basics to a quite high level of playing in a short time. The only drawback with learning electric guitar at home on your own is that you don&#8217;t have anyone beside you to point out any bad playing habits you might be forming. These if left unchecked can become a major problem later on.</p>
<p>A good guide is to get a home study course on electric <a href="http://www.learnguitarelectric.com/go/jamorama1.html"  rel='nofollow' >guitar for beginners</a> and then once a month or so take a one on one lesson with a professional just to make sure you stay on the right path.</p>
